explanation: This solution first checks if the concatenation of the two strings is equal to the concatenation of the second string with the first. If not, it returns an empty string. If they are equal, it calculates the GCD of the lengths of the two strings and returns the substring of the first string from the start to the GCD length. The GCD calculation is done using the Euclidean algorithm, which has a time complexity of O(1).

